title: IEF, EMTY: Big ETF Inflows - Nasdaq.com
text: Comparing units outstanding versus one week ago at the coverage universe of ETFs at ETF Channel, the biggest inflow was seen in the iShares 7-10 Year Treasury Bond ETF, which added 5,100,000 units, or a 3.1% increase week over week.    makeArticleAd();  And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest increase in inflows was the ProShares ProShares Decline of the Retail Store ETF, which added 75,000 units, for a 37.5% increase in outstanding units.
